---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import { loadCategories } from "../../lib/generated";

const categories = await loadCategories();

const canonical = "https://freeperlcode.com/functions";
---

<Base
  title="Perl Functions Reference - Built-ins & Patterns"
  description="Perl function reference for core and common utilities-syntax, parameters, return values, pitfalls, context rules, and examples you can paste into code."
  canonical={canonical}
>
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Perl Functions Reference: Built-In Functions, Syntax, and Practical Examples</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
      Welcome to Free Perl Code's <strong>Perl functions reference</strong>-a fast, searchable guide to the
      <strong>built-in functions</strong> you use every day, with clear explanations, edge cases, and
      copy-paste-ready <strong>Perl examples</strong>. Whether you're learning the language from scratch
      or leveling up an existing codebase, this page is designed as a friendly <strong>Perl tutorial</strong>
      that helps you move from "I've seen this function" to "I can use it correctly under pressure."
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
      Perl's standard library is famously rich: concise text processing, flexible data structures, and powerful
      file and system utilities. The trick is knowing which function fits your problem, what it returns in scalar
      vs list context, and how it behaves with real-world input (empty strings, undefined values, Unicode, large
      files, and messy logs). This reference focuses on the essentials: what a function does, what it expects,
      what it returns, and common patterns you can reuse immediately.
    </p>

    <div class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What You'll Find in This Functions Guide</h2>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-perl-500">String Functions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Need to clean input, format output, or extract a value from text? Perl shines here. Learn how to use
          string functions like <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">length</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">substr</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">index</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">uc</code>,
          <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">lc</code>, and <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">sprintf</code> to transform data safely. You'll also see practical notes on
          trimming whitespace, handling undefined values, and building readable output for CLIs and web responses.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-perl-500">Array Functions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Arrays power most everyday Perl workflows: collecting records, iterating results, batching jobs, and
          assembling output. This section covers array functions such as <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">push</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">pop</code>,
          <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">shift</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">unshift</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">splice</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">sort</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">grep</code>,
          and <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">map</code>. Each entry includes common idioms (filtering, transforming, deduplicating) and
          examples that emphasize readability and performance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-perl-500">Hash Functions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Hashes are Perl's go-to structure for lookups, grouping, counting, and configuration. Explore patterns for
          <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">keys</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">values</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">each</code>, and safe existence checks with
          <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">exists</code> and <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">defined</code>. You'll find examples for frequency tables, grouping rows by
          a field, merging options, and building robust defaults-exactly the kinds of tasks you hit in scripts and
          production services.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-perl-500">File Functions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          From simple scripts to ETL pipelines, file work is unavoidable. Learn reliable approaches using
          <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">open</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">close</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">readline</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">print</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">printf</code>,
          <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">seek</code>, and file tests like <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">-e</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">-f</code>, and <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">-d</code>. We also
          highlight safe patterns for encoding, line-by-line processing, and error handling so your tools behave well
          on servers and in cron jobs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-perl-500">Regex and Pattern Matching</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Perl's regex engine is legendary, and the right function-level building blocks make it even more effective.
          This guide includes idioms with <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">split</code>, <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">join</code>, and match operators for extracting,
          validating, and rewriting text. You'll see examples for parsing logs, validating user input, and performing
          targeted substitutions-without turning your code into an unreadable wall of punctuation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-perl-50 dark:bg-dark-800 border border-perl-200 dark:border-dark-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Learn Faster with a Reference + Tutorial Approach</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          Use this page as both a <strong>Perl tutorial</strong> and a quick <strong>Perl functions reference</strong>:
          skim the category you need, open a function entry, and grab a working snippet. If you're new to Perl, start
          with strings and arrays, then move into hashes, file handling, and regex. If you're experienced, jump
          straight to the function you need and compare return values, contexts, and gotchas. Either way, you'll build
          real confidence with <strong>Perl examples</strong> grounded in practical tasks and <strong>built-in functions</strong>
          you can rely on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Function Categories</h2>

      {categories.length === 0 ? (
        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-dark-800">
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            No categories exported yet. Run the data pipeline first.
          </p>
        </div>
      ) : (
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          {categories.map((c) => (
            <a
              href={`/topics/${c.slug}`}
              class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 hover:border-perl-500 dark:hover:border-perl-500 transition-colors bg-white dark:bg-dark-900"
            >
              <div class="font-semibold mb-2">{c.name}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                {c.indexable} published â€¢ {c.verified} verified
              </div>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Common Perl Built-in Functions</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-perl-500">String Functions</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">length</code> - Get string length</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">substr</code> - Extract substring</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">index</code> - Find substring position</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">uc</code> / <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">lc</code> - Change case</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">split</code> - Split string into list</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">join</code> - Join list into string</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-perl-500">Array Functions</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">push</code> - Add element to end</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">pop</code> - Remove last element</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">shift</code> - Remove first element</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">unshift</code> - Add to beginning</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">splice</code> - Remove/replace elements</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">sort</code> - Sort array</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-perl-500">Hash Functions</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">keys</code> - Get all keys</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">values</code> - Get all values</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">each</code> - Iterate key-value pairs</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">exists</code> - Check key existence</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">delete</code> - Remove key</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-perl-500">File Functions</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">open</code> - Open file handle</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">close</code> - Close file handle</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">readline</code> / <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">&lt;&gt;</code> - Read line</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">print</code> - Write to file</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">say</code> - Write with newline</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">eof</code> - Check end of file</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-perl-500">Regular Expressions</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">m//</code> - Pattern match</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">s///</code> - Substitution</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">tr///</code> - Transliteration</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">qr//</code> - Quote regex</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">split</code> - Split by pattern</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">grep</code> - Filter by pattern</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-perl-500">Special Variables</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">$_</code> - Default variable</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">@_</code> - Subroutine arguments</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">$.</code> - Current line number</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">$!</code> - System error string</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">$?</code> - Child error status</li>
            <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-dark-800 px-1 rounded">@ARGV</code> - Command line args</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-perl-50 dark:bg-dark-800 border border-perl-200 dark:border-dark-700">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Looking for a Specific Function?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Use our AI-powered search to find detailed explanations and examples for any Perl function.
        Just describe what you're looking for in plain English.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/search"
        class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-perl-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-perl-600 transition-colors"
      >
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 21l-6-6m2-5a7 7 0 11-14 0 7 7 0 0114 0z"></path>
        </svg>
        Search Functions
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Related Resources</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>
          <a href="/topics" class="text-perl-500 hover:underline">
            Browse by Topic &rarr;
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/questions" class="text-perl-500 hover:underline">
            All Questions &rarr;
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://perldoc.perl.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-perl-500 hover:underline">
            Official Perl Documentation &rarr;
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://metacpan.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-perl-500 hover:underline">
            MetaCPAN &rarr;
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
